---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="About | Filecoin Data Portal"
  description="Background, licensing, and usage details for Filecoin Data Portal datasets."
>
  <section class="page-header" aria-labelledby="about-title">
    <h1 id="about-title">About</h1>
    <p>
      The Filecoin Data Portal is an open and local friendly data platform that
      unifies Filecoin data from diverse sources, on chain and off chain. It is
      an instance of <a href="https://github.com/datonic/datadex">Datadex</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="about-faq" aria-labelledby="faq-title">
    <h2 id="faq-title" class="section-title">FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How much do these datasets cost</h3>
      <p>
        All datasets are free to use. They are available to anyone at no cost
        without warranties or guarantees of any kind, either expressed or
        implied. By using these datasets, you agree that you do so at your own
        risk.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Are there restrictions on how these datasets can be used</h3>
      <p>
        Datasets can be used without restriction. They are released under a
        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/public-domain/cc0/"
          >CC0 license into the public domain</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Who is using these datasets</h3>
      <p>
        Datasets produced by the Filecoin Data Portal are used by a wide range of
        organizations and individuals. Example use cases include the following.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://pulse.filecoindataportal.xyz/">Filecoin Pulse</a>.</li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://numbers.filecoindataportal.xyz/">Filecoin In Numbers</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://dune.com/kalen/filecoin-daily-metrics">Dune Dashboard</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.reppo.ai/models"
            >Reppo Storage Provider reputation models</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://fidl.tech">FIDL</a>'s
          <a
            href="https://compliance.allocator.tech/report/f03014641/1723421684/report.md"
            >Allocator compliance reports</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How does the data get updated</h3>
      <p>
        Data updates daily via GitHub Actions. You can review
        <a href="https://github.com/davidgasquez/filecoin-data-portal/actions"
          >all runs and logs in the repository</a
        >.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How can I get the data</h3>
      <p>
        Data is available in multiple formats. Go to the <a href="/datasets"
          >datasets page</a
        > and select the format that suits your needs. If you need more,
        <a href="https://github.com/davidgasquez/filecoin-data-portal/issues/new"
          >open an issue</a
        > and we can help.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Who is behind this project</h3>
      <p>
        This project is maintained by <a href="https://davidgasquez.com/"
          >David Gasquez</a
        > thanks to
        <a href="https://protocol.ai/blog/pl-past-present-future/"
          >Protocol Labs blue funds</a
        > and
        <a href="https://www.fil-retropgf.io/"
          >Filecoin Retroactive Public Goods Funding</a
        > programs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    max-inline-size: 40rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .about-faq {
    max-inline-size: 40rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-block: var(--space-4);
  }

  .faq-item:last-child {
    border-block-end: none;
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    margin-block: 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin-block: 0;
  }

  .faq-item ul {
    margin-block: var(--space-2) 0;
  }

  .faq-item li + li {
    margin-block-start: var(--space-1);
  }
</style>
